The front of the polluted water of Songhua River in northeast China reached Harbin, capital of Heilongjiang Province, on early morning.
China has informed Russia of the water pollution situation in the country's northeastern Songhua River.
The Nov. 13 blast in Jilin, a city in Jilin province, caused massive amounts of benzene, a toxic, flammable liquid to flow into the Songhua River.
Two reservoirs on the Songhua River reinforced water discharge to dilute a massive slick of chemical pollutants floating through this capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang.
